OL,4,Cmake protein source more appealing'
OL,6,FAlmost half (47%) said they would not
OL,7,Fbe willing to eat insects, while 40%
OL,8,Fsaid they were unsure.
OL,10,FOnly 13% of people who completed the
OL,11,Fsurvey said they would be willing to
OL,12,Fregularly consume insects.
OL,14,FPresenting the findings at the
OL,15,FEuropean Congress on Obesity in
OL,16,FVenice, Dr Maxine Sharps, of De
OL,17,FMontfort University, said: "The
OL,18,Fdisgust factor associated with eating
OL,19,Fwhole insects could be overcome by
OL,20,Fincorporating insect flours into
OL,21,Fprocessed foods.
